{"mode": "append", "content": ",
  {
    "speaker": "SPEAKER_01",
    "text": "How does our environment shape our financial psychology?",
    "emo_text": "Inquisitive",
    "emo_alpha": 0.6,
    "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00022"]
  },
  {
    "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
    "text": "Environment is critical. You can create friction for behaviors you want to avoid—like not keeping cookies at home—and eliminate friction for the things that align with your goals.",
    "emo_text": "Practical advice",
    "emo_alpha": 0.6,
    "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00023"]
  },
  {
    "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
    "text": "It's also about who you're around. If you're surrounded by money‑status people, you're more likely to spend to keep up. And we can manage cognitive load by offering fewer choices.",
    "emo_text": "Expanding",
    "emo_alpha": 0.6,
    "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00023"]
  },
  {
    "speaker": "SPEAKER_00",
    "text": "What are money scripts?",
    "emo_text": "Curious",
    "emo_alpha": 0.6,
    "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00035"]
  },
  {
    "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
    "text": "Money scripts are unconscious beliefs about money that form early—like being money avoidant, money worship, money status, or vigilant. Knowing your script helps you anticipate hurdles.",
    "emo_text": "Explaining",
    "emo_alpha": 0.6,
    "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00035"]
  }"}

{"mode": "append", "content": ",
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_01",
   "text": "What role does identity play in goal setting?",
   "emo_text": "Thoughtful",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00048"]
 },
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
   "text": "A huge role. Goals are far more sustainable when they're tied to our identity—like seeing yourself as a provider or a mentor. That shapes what's meaningful versus what's just expected.",
   "emo_text": "Insightful",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00049"]
 },
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_00",
   "text": "How well do people tend to understand their own risk tolerance?",
   "emo_text": "Curious",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00062"]
 },
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
   "text": "It's like race‑car driving and sex—everyone thinks they're good at it. People overestimate their tolerance when markets are up, and that's where recency bias kicks in.",
   "emo_text": "Wry analogy",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00063"]
 },
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_00",
   "text": "What's the difference between psychometric and revealed‑preference risk questionnaires?",
   "emo_text": "Technical inquiry",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00070"]
 },
 {
   "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
   "text": "Psychometric tools assess attitudes and beliefs—how risk feels. Revealed preference infers tolerance from past or hypothetical behaviors. Psychometrics bring in the emotional and behavioral pieces for a more complete picture.",
   "emo_text": "Clarifying",
   "emo_alpha": 0.6,
   "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00071", "seg_00073"]
 }"}

{"mode": "append", "content": ",
 {
  "speaker": "SPEAKER_01",
  "text": "How does the full set of information from MRI help someone make better financial decisions?",
  "emo_text": "Practical question",
  "emo_alpha": 0.6,
  "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00080"]
 },
 {
  "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
  "text": "It helps you understand yourself better—your irrational behaviors, your history. That lets you alter your environment and align your actions with your goals.",
  "emo_text": "Reflective",
  "emo_alpha": 0.6,
  "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00081"]
 },
 {
  "speaker": "SPEAKER_01",
  "text": "Last question: how do you define success in your life?",
  "emo_text": "Personal inquiry",
  "emo_alpha": 0.6,
  "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00082"]
 },
 {
  "speaker": "SPEAKER_02",
  "text": "If you want your life to matter, everything you do has to matter. That means aligning your environment, the people around you, and your behaviors with what's meaningful.",
  "emo_text": "Philosophical",
  "emo_alpha": 0.6,
  "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00083"]
 },
 {
  "speaker": "SPEAKER_00",
  "text": "Thanks, Charles. This has been a great conversation.",
  "emo_text": "Grateful wrap‑up",
  "emo_alpha": 0.6,
  "source_segment_ids": ["seg_00084"]
 }"}

